parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of heat shields can cause the vehicle's engine and surrounding components to overheat, leading to premature wear, reduced performance, and potentially even engine failure.
The failure of the oil sending unit can cause the vehicle's engine to operate with inadequate lubrication, leading to premature wear, engine damage, and potentially even engine failure.
Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
